        "text": "Remark: The above solution is deliberately more verbose than is really necessary. A shorter way to say this is that any two distinct rational points determine a rational line (a line of the form ax + by + c = 0 with a, b, c rational), while any two nonparallel rational lines intersect at a rational point. A similar statement holds with the rational numbers replaced by any field.",
